Ah ha, let me think now. One of my philosophies was - what was it now - forgotten - now let me get it right, there is no justice in the world. Don't expect it. You'd have to fight for it, no justice. Do
n't expect it, don't expect justice. I'm told - I'm told that - that's a most abominable thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4549223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620346\charrsid5339606 Did you get this idea about having to fight for justice from the fact that there was little justice at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4007407 JC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620346\charrsid5339606 There wasn't much justice at school, 
no. I was punished for things I never did. Then I got used to that, and I began to accept it. Which - in the revolutionary attitude of today would be considered absolutely abominable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4549223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620346\charrsid5339606 But you said you had to fight for justice so you must have felt to a certain extent that it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4007407 JC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620346\charrsid5339606 Oh of course I felt it was wrong. But I took it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4549223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620346\charrsid5339606 When you were at Tonbridge and you used to come home for holidays what did you used to do with your time then?
